snippet.textDisplay: Hi, I’m from Brooklyn and if you are ever planning to move to New York City you NEED to save money and be prepared for the 1,000+ rent. I recommend that you save 5,000$ .It might seem like a lot but trust me, You need to be prepared. If you have more, you could possibly find a condo but the condos seem to be around 100,000$. Lastly, If you move to New York, a regular 2 bedroom apartment could cost you 3,000$+. A Studio apartment is possibly the cheapest apartment you could get for a minimum of 1,500+. (Unless you apply for affordable housing).

ok but now we want to see an apartment tour/makeover girl! i live for these videos on your channel (that's how i discovered it actually!). i recently moved in an apartment alone for the first time in my life and youtube just sprung your last apartment makeover on me like "hey bitch look at this your place will nEvER look this good, and look at this girl you'll never look so good either" lol and honestly i think i have watched every single video on your channel since then (cause you're cool af girl).
I live in France btw, so the rent prices in NY shook me hArRd but i loved the tips you gave, tbh they're not very useful from a french perspective (since the laws, fees etc aren't the same) but the few tips about what to be careful about in the building, the neighborhood and stuff like that are spot on, cause they're actually relatable no matter which city you live in.
Anyway, i'm gonna shut up now, love your videos, so happy you found such a lovely place, like i genuinely feel so happy for you and like a proud mom ???? Even tho we're about the same age ???? xo
